article.headline: E. Kentucky 84, Delaware St. 51
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Glenn Cosey scored 21 points to help Eastern Kentucky dominate Delaware State 84-51 Wednesday night in nonconference action. Delaware State (3-5) led 2-0 early, but that would be its only lead as Eastern Kentucky would dominate the remainder of the half. Eastern Kentucky (6-0) made 8 of 18 3-pointers in the first half, with Cosey connecting on 4 of 5 3s to help the Colonels lead at halftime 43-23. Delaware State was unable to make it a contest in the second half. Eastern Kentucky used a 15-0 run to go up 74-39 and put the game out of reach. Mike DiNunno and Eric Stutz scored 11 points apiece for the Colonels, and Marcus Lewis came off the bench and added 15 points. Miles Bowman Jr. finished with 15 points and 13 rebounds to lead Delaware State. Eastern Kentucky is 6-0 for the first time since the 1946-47 season.
